00:36:57.180 --> 00:36:58.110 align:middle line:90%
>>HATSIS: Yes, exactly.

00:36:58.110 --> 00:36:59.570 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Yeah,
calling upon them.

00:36:59.570 --> 00:37:00.460 align:middle line:90%
>>HATSIS: Yeah.

00:37:00.460 --> 00:37:04.650 align:middle line:84%
She used her ointment to imagine
she was turning into a cat.

00:37:04.650 --> 00:37:08.050 align:middle line:84%
And it's possible that that has
some shamanistic underpinnings

00:37:08.050 --> 00:37:09.700 align:middle line:84%
to it, just like
Siberian shamans

00:37:09.700 --> 00:37:12.059 align:middle line:84%
and other people and
Peruvian shamanism.

00:37:12.059 --> 00:37:13.600 align:middle line:84%
It's possible that
there is some kind

00:37:13.600 --> 00:37:15.290 align:middle line:90%
of cross-cultural connection.

00:37:15.290 --> 00:37:17.460 align:middle line:90%
But we don't exactly know.

00:37:17.460 --> 00:37:19.640 align:middle line:84%
I hypothesize it
was used that way

00:37:19.640 --> 00:37:21.360 align:middle line:90%
because she was a wise woman.

00:37:21.360 --> 00:37:22.960 align:middle line:84%
But there's really
no way to know.

00:37:22.960 --> 00:37:25.344 align:middle line:84%
Now, as far as another type
of these kinds of animal

00:37:25.344 --> 00:37:26.760 align:middle line:84%
transformations,
it seemed to just

00:37:26.760 --> 00:37:29.360 align:middle line:84%
be a form of entertainment,
like on a boring

00:37:29.360 --> 00:37:32.690 align:middle line:84%
Saturday, like I mentioned
